Challenge Rules: (Regular)

01. The playthrough has to be completed within 1.5 hours/ 90 minutes, starting as soon as the alarm is audible after the starting event.
02.	The playthrough must be played on game version 1.3.11 or newer.
03.	The console cannot be used for any purpose during the playthrough. (No STFU either!)
04.	Map seed must be shown blank at the begging of the game.
05.	The playthrough can be played on: Safe, Euclid or Keter difficulty.
06.	Intro Sequence can be skipped if desired.
07.	Custom difficulty is not allowed.
08.	Class D Orientation Leaflet, given to you after/during intro sequence cannot be dropped.
09.	Document SCP-173, given to you after/during intro sequence cannot be dropped.
10.	Any “newly” acquired items during playthrough cannot be dropped.
11.	Taking off the hazmat suit after equipping it is not allowed as this results in dropping the item.


Combining/ using items to free up inventory slots: (Regular)

01.	Storing quarters, keycards and SCP-860 in the wallet is allowed.
02.	Storing documents on the clipboard is allowed.
03.	Putting batteries inside of night vision goggles, navigators and radios is allowed.
04.	Combining SCP-148 with either a gas mask or hazmat suit in SCP-914 is allowed.
05.	Removing quarters from the wallet to use them with SCP-294 is allowed.
06.	Keycards inside wallets can be “used” to open doors.
07.	Using pills, eyedrops, first aid kits, syringes, strange bottles and cigarettes is allowed.
08.	Combined items cannot be taken apart after being combined unless stated otherwise.
09.	Removing keycards from the wallet for reasons other than opening doors is not allowed.
10.	Using pills, eyedrops, first aid kits, syringes, strange bottles and cigarettes is allowed.


SCP-914 Rules: (Regular)

01.	Dropping items inside SCP-914’s intake booth to “refine” them is allowed.
02.	Destroying items with SCP-914 using the Rough setting is allowed.
03.	Leaving items inside SCP-914’s outtake booth, temporally freeing inventory slots is not allowed.
04.	Dropping items anywhere outside of SCP-914’s intake booth is not allowed.
05.	All items inside SCP-914’s outtake booth must be picked up again, even if they harm the player. 


Additional Challenge Rules: (Hard)

01.	All rules for the “Regular” challenge apply unless overruled by the ones below.
02. The playthrough has to be completed within 3.0 hours/ 180 minutes, starting as soon as the alarm is audible after the starting event.
03.	The playthrough must be played on Euclid or Keter difficulty.
04.	Safe and Custom difficulties are not allowed.

SCP-914 Rules: (Hard)

01.	SCP-914 can only be used once to upgrade a level 2 keycard to a level 3 keycard.
02.	Using SCP-914 for anything else is not allowed.
